  "caption": "Figure 4. Benyviridae. Phylogenetic tree based on the codon-aligned nucleotide sequences of the RdRp protein domains of benyviruses and other related viruses. The analysis and abbreviations are as in Figure 3. Benyviridae and the tree with the highest log likelihood (-21239.3562) is shown. Additional virus abbreviations are: HBBLV: Hubei beny-like virus 1 (unclassified); HEV: human hepatitis E virus ( Orthohepevirus , Hepeviridae ); MPTLV: Macrophomina phaseolina tobamo-like virus (unclassified); RUBV: rubella virus ( Rubivirus , Togaviridae ). This phylogenetic tree and corresponding sequence alignment are available to download from the Resources page .",
